<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF108-468-444  </DOCNO><DOCID>08 468 444.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Electronic News  May 21 1990 v36 n1810 p28(1).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>$10M U.S. technology program gets firm, group support. (AdvancedTechnology Program)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Connelly, Joanne.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>The US Advanced Technology Program has firm support fromcompanies, research labs and trade associations, but there isstill question about the Department of Commerce's specific plansfor implementation, funding levels, and licensing or royaltyarrangements.andP;  The Department of Commerce National Institute ofStandards and Technology (NIST) will assist US companies or jointventures in research and development plans on procompetitive,generic technologies.andP;  Under the plan, the US government wouldaward grants and create cooperative research agreements for thedevelopment of technology that would benefit the economy.andO;Comments solicited by NIST range from Bellcore suggestion thatNIST broaden the areas of technology to a suggestion that theCommerce Department narrow the scope of the ATP program.andP;  Oneexecutive believes that half of initial funding be used for theelectronics industry.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Topic:     Research and DevelopmentGovernment AgencyUnited States. Department of CommerceUnited States. National Institute of Standards and Technology.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>